flowchart TD
  A[Steward opens New Domain form] --> B{Which kind of domain?}

  B -->|Use a subdomain of the host domain — default| C[Enter just the label, e.g. tenant-a]
  C --> D[Stimulus controller computes label + . + host apex client-side]
  D --> E[Hostname field auto-filled: tenant-a.btsdev.ca]

  B -->|Use my own domain| F[DNS/TLS guidance panel shown]
  F --> G[Steward types the full external hostname directly]
  G --> H[Hostname field: app.clientdomain.example]

  E --> I[Submit — POST platform_domains]
  H --> I

  I --> J{PlatformDomain validations: unique hostname, primary/share exclusivity}
  J -->|Invalid| K[422 — re-render with errors]
  J -->|Valid| L[PlatformDomain saved]

  L --> M[Operational step — NOT automated by this UI]
  M --> N[Subdomain path: covered by existing wildcard cert + DNS record on the host domain — usually no extra ops step]
  M --> O[Custom domain path: client must add their own CNAME/A record; operator must provision a dedicated TLS cert via SNI]

  N --> P[PlatformContextMiddleware resolves this hostname on the next request]
  O --> P

  classDef decision fill:#fff8e1,stroke:#8a6d00,color:#5f4b00;
  classDef subdomain fill:#e6f4ea,stroke:#137333,color:#0d652d;
  classDef custom fill:#e8f0fe,stroke:#1a56db,color:#1e3a8a;
  classDef ops fill:#fce8e6,stroke:#b3261e,color:#5f2120;
  class B,J decision;
  class C,D,E,N subdomain;
  class F,G,H,O custom;
  class M ops;
